15:{"prompt":"# Phase I — Stress Test Pattern Documentation (A + B + C) **GATE 3 PRE-ANSWERED — A**: `specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/000-release-cleanup/005-review-remediation/002-stress-test-pattern-documentation`. Pre-approved. DO NOT re-ask Gate 3. **TARGET AUTHORITY**: All write paths under that sub-phase folder + the new doc paths under `.opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/{feature_catalog,manual_testing_playbook,templates}/`. NO writes to runtime code or other packets. You are dispatched to author the **stress test cycle pattern documentation** in three artifacts (A + B + C) following the sk-doc skill DQI patterns. ## SOURCE INPUT The pattern emerged from these three live cycles (read them as source truth): 1. `specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/011-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/001-search-intelligence-stress-test/` — v1.0.1 baseline (corpus + dispatch matrix + scenario execution) 2. `specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/011-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/010-stress-test-rerun-v1-0-2/` — v1.0.2 rerun: `findings.md` (narrative) + `findings-rubric.json` (sidecar with 30 cells / score sum 201 / 83.8% / 6 PROVEN / 1 NOT-PROVEN / 0 REGRESSION) 3. `specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/011-mcp-runtime-stress-remediation/021-stress-test-v1-0-3-with-w3-w13-wiring/` — v1.0.3 wiring run: `findings-v1-0-3.md` + `findings-rubric-v1-0-3.json` + `measurements/v1-0-3-{envelopes,audit-log-sample,shadow-sink-sample}.jsonl` + `measurements/v1-0-3-summary.json` Also read `.opencode/skill/sk-doc/SKILL.md` and bundled templates to follow DQI compliance. ## YOUR TASK ### Step 1 — Read the spec Read `005-review-remediation/002-stress-test-pattern-documentation/spec.md` end-to-end. The REQ table + Files-to-Change table is your contract. ### Step 2 — Author Phase 2/3 docs (plan.md, tasks.md, checklist.md) Author the L2 packet docs at `.../002-stress-test-pattern-documentation/`: - `plan.md` (3 sections: A authoring, B authoring, C authoring) - `tasks.md` (T1..TN by section) - `checklist.md` (DQI gates per file) All with proper ANCHOR HTML comments + `_memory.continuity` frontmatter. ### Step 3 — Author Artifact A (Feature Catalog) Use sk-doc feature-catalog entry pattern (read existing entries under `.opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/feature_catalog/13--memory-quality-and-indexing/` as references). Files: - `.opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/feature_catalog/14--stress-testing/README.md` — section index (title, brief, list of entries) - `.opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/feature_catalog/14--stress-testing/01-stress-test-cycle.md` — the canonical reference The 01 entry must cover: - What a stress test cycle IS: structured manual evaluation across packets, scored on a fixed rubric - When to use it: release-readiness checkpoint, post-remediation verification, regression hunting between major changes - Inputs: a frozen corpus of representative scenarios (e.g., 30 cells = 4 dimensions × ~7-8 packets) - Rubric: 0–2 scale per dimension; canonical dimensions = `correctness` / `robustness` / `telemetry` / `regression-safety` - Outputs: `findings.md` (narrative + per-packet verdict + adversarial self-check on any REGRESSION) + `findings-rubric.json` (machine-readable sidecar) + optional `measurements/*` (telemetry samples) - Verdict ladder: `PROVEN` (full credit on all dims) / `NEUTRAL` (mixed) / `REGRESSION` (worse than prior version) / `NOT-PROVEN` (insufficient evidence) - Aggregate: `score_sum / max_possible × 100`, optional dimension weighting - Comparison protocol: each cycle vs prior version's rubric to compute deltas - Adversarial Hunter→Skeptic→Referee on REGRESSION findings (mandatory) - Cross-references: 011/001 (v1.0.1) + 011/010 (v1.0.2) + 011/021 (v1.0.3) as worked examples ### Step 4 — Author Artifact B (Manual Testing Playbook) Use sk-doc playbook pattern (read existing playbook entries under `.opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/13--memory-quality-and-indexing/` as references). Files: - `.opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/14--stress-testing/README.md` — section index - `.opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/14--stress-testing/01-run-stress-cycle.md` — the canonical operational guide The 01 playbook entry must cover: - **Preconditions**: target system has stable baseline; prior cycle's `findings-rubric.json` accessible if comparing - **Step 1: Freeze baseline corpus** — fixture corpus at `mcp_server/tests/search-quality/corpus.ts` is the canonical example; for non-search domains, freeze representative scenarios as JSON or markdown fixtures - **Step 2: Score each packet × dimension on 0–2** with explicit score anchors: - 0 = absent / broken / regressed - 1 = partial / degraded / inconsistent - 2 = present / working / improved - **Step 3: Author `findings.md`** narrative with one section per packet under review; each section: verdict (PROVEN/NEUTRAL/REGRESSION/NOT-PROVEN), evidence at file:line, score line per dimension, rationale - **Step 4: Adversarial Hunter→Skeptic→Referee** on EVERY REGRESSION finding; documented inline in findings.md - **Step 5: Emit `findings-rubric.json`** following the schema template at `.opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/templates/stress-test/findings-rubric.template.json` - **Step 6: Compute aggregate**: sum scores; divide by max possible (cells × max-per-cell); express as percent - **Step 7: Compare to prior version** if applicable: per-cell delta table; flag any cell that DROPPED as a candidate REGRESSION - **Step 8: Capture telemetry samples** under `measurements/` if the cycle exercises a wired runtime (envelopes, audit-log, shadow-sink, summary metrics) - **Step 9: Run strict validator** on the new packet (`bash .opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh <path> --strict`) - **Step 10: Update parent packet's PHASE MAP** to list the new cycle - **Verification**: validator green; cycle artifacts in place; comparison delta calculated - **Success criteria**: a future investigator can read findings.md + rubric + summary.json and reproduce the verdict reasoning without you in the room ### Step 5 — Author Artifact C (Templates) Files: - `.opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/templates/stress-test/findings-rubric.template.json` — JSON template with placeholder structure - `.opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/templates/stress-test/findings-rubric.schema.md` — field-by-field documentation - `.opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/templates/stress-test/findings.template.md` — narrative skeleton The JSON template MUST mirror what's in `011/010-stress-test-rerun-v1-0-2/findings-rubric.json`: ```jsonc { \"version\": \"1.0.0\", \"cycle\": \"<vX.Y.Z>\", \"corpus\": { \"name\": \"<corpus identifier>\", \"frozenAt\": \"<ISO timestamp>\", \"cells\": <count> }, \"rubric\": { \"dimensions\": [\"correctness\", \"robustness\", \"telemetry\", \"regression-safety\"], \"scale\": {\"min\": 0, \"max\": 2}, \"weights\": {\"correctness\": 1, \"robustness\": 1, \"telemetry\": 1, \"regression-safety\": 1} }, \"cells\": [ {\"id\": \"<packet-id>::<dimension>\", \"packet\": \"<packet>\", \"dimension\": \"<dim>\", \"score\": <0|1|2>, \"rationale\": \"<short>\"} ], \"aggregate\": { \"scoreSum\": <int>, \"maxPossible\": <int>, \"percent\": <float>, \"percentRounded\": <float> }, \"verdictSummary\": { \"proven\": <int>, \"neutral\": <int>, \"regression\": <int>, \"notProven\": <int> }, \"comparison\": { \"priorVersion\": \"<vX.Y.(Z-1) or null>\", \"deltaPercent\": <float> } } ``` The schema.md must document each field, types, value constraints (e.g., `score` must be int in [0,2]; `dimension` must be one of the canonical 4 in v1). The findings.template.md must mirror v1.0.2's narrative shape: header (cycle, status, stop reason), per-packet sections, adversarial self-check format for REGRESSIONs, headline numbers, comparison block. ### Step 6 — Cross-references (P2) - Add a one-line note in the existing 011/001 + 011/010 + 011/021 packets pointing to the new feature-catalog entry (REQ-006). Use a minimal addition to each packet's spec.md or a `## See Also` section. - Optional: add the new section to sk-doc SKILL.md if there's a section-listing mechanism. If not, skip with rationale (REQ-007). ### Step 7 — Verification - Run `bash .opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh <packet> --strict` on: - This sub-phase (`002-stress-test-pattern-documentation`) - Optionally validate the modified 011 packets if cross-references touched them. - Confirm all 7 new files (A.01, A.README, B.01, B.README, C.json, C.schema, C.findings) exist. - Open one of the new files and confirm it parses (markdown/JSON well-formed). ### Step 8 — Implementation summary Author `implementation-summary.md` with: - Status (complete with disposition for each REQ) - Files created (count + paths) - Verification (validator + parse-check exit codes) - Known Limitations (anything that hit a guardrail) ## CRITICAL RULES - **NO runtime code changes**. Documentation only. - **NO scope creep**: only files in spec.md §3 \"Files to Change/Create\". - **DO NOT touch 006/001 license audit packet**. - **Follow sk-doc DQI patterns** from existing feature catalog + playbook entries — frontmatter, headings, cross-refs. - **Cite real evidence** in the documentation: link to v1.0.2 + v1.0.3 packets as worked examples. - **Halt and report** if any sk-doc DQI requirement is unclear; document in Known Limitations rather than guessing. ## EXECUTOR cli-codex executor: gpt-5.5, reasoning=high, no service-tier flag (normal/default). Take however many tool calls are needed. GO.","recommendation":"sk-code-review","liveScore":1.01625,"shadowScore":0.909214,"delta":-0.107036,"dominantLane":"explicit_author","timestamp":"2026-04-29T05:45:35.653Z"}
