ated - **Success criteria**: a future investigator can read findings.md + rubric + summary.json and reproduce the verdict reasoning without you in the room ### Step 5 — Author Artifact C (Templates) Files: - `.opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/templates/stress-test/findings-rubric.template.json` — JSON template with placeholder structure - `.opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/templates/stress-test/findings-rubric.schema.md` — field-by-field documentation - `.opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/templates/stress-test/findings.template.md` — narrative skeleton The JSON template MUST mirror what's in `011/010-stress-test-rerun-v1-0-2/findings-rubric.json`: ```jsonc { \"version\": \"1.0.0\", \"cycle\": \"<vX.Y.Z>\", \"corpus\": { \"name\": \"<corpus identifier>\", \"frozenAt\": \"<ISO timestamp>\", \"cells\": <count> }, \"rubric\": { \"dimensions\": [\"correctness\", \"robustness\", \"telemetry\", \"regression-safety\"], \"scale\": {\"min\": 0, \"max\": 2}, \"weights\": {\"correctness\": 1, \"robustness\": 1, \"telemetry\": 1, \"regression-safety\": 1} }, \"cells\": [ {\"id\": \"<packet-id>::<dimension>\", \"packet\": \"<packet>\", \"dimension\": \"<dim>\", \"score\": <0|1|2>, \"rationale\": \"<short>\"} ], \"aggregate\": { \"scoreSum\": <int>, \"maxPossible\": <int>, \"percent\": <float>, \"percentRounded\": <float> }, \"verdictSummary\": { \"proven\": <int>, \"neutral\": <int>, \"regression\": <int>, \"notProven\": <int> }, \"comparison\": { \"priorVersion\": \"<vX.Y.(Z-1) or null>\", \"deltaPercent\": <float> } } ``` The schema.md must document each field, types, value constraints (e.g., `score` must be int in [0,2]; `dimension` must be one of the canonical 4 in v1). The findings.template.md must mirror v1.0.2's narrative shape: header (cycle, status, stop reason), per-packet sections, adversarial self-check format for REGRESSIONs, headline numbers, comparison block. ### Step 6 — Cross-references (P2) - Add a one-line note in the existing 011/001 + 011/010 + 011/021 packets pointing to the new feature-catalog entry (REQ-006). Use a minimal addition to each packet's spec.md or a `## See Also` section. - Optional: add the new section to sk-doc SKILL.md if there's a section-listing mechanism. If not, skip with rationale (REQ-007). ### Step 7 — Verification - Run `bash .opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh <packet> --strict` on: - This sub-phase (`002-stress-test-pattern-documentation`) - Optionally validate the modified 011 packets if cross-references touched them. - Confirm all 7 new files (A.01, A.README, B.01, B.README, C.json, C.schema, C.findings) exist. - Open one of the new files and confirm it parses (markdown/JSON well-formed). ### Step 8 — Implementation summary Author `implementation-summary.md` with: - Status (complete with disposition for each REQ) - Files created (count + paths) - Verification (validator + parse-check exit codes) - Known Limitations (anything that hit a guardrail) ## CRITICAL RULES - **NO runtime code changes**. Documentation only. - **NO scope creep**: only files in spec.md §3 \"Files to Change/Create\". - **DO NOT touch 006/001 license audit packet**. - **Follow sk-doc DQI patterns** from existing feature catalog + playbook entries — frontmatter, headings, cross-refs. - **Cite real evidence** in the documentation: link to v1.0.2 + v1.0.3 packets as worked examples. - **Halt and report** if any sk-doc DQI requirement is unclear; document in Known Limitations rather than guessing. ## EXECUTOR cli-codex executor: gpt-5.5, reasoning=high, no service-tier flag (normal/default). Take however many tool calls are needed. GO.","recommendation":"sk-doc","liveScore":0.954,"shadowScore":0.827666,"delta":-0.126334,"dominantLane":"explicit_author","timestamp":"2026-04-29T05:45:35.653Z"}
